      • onShow

        public void onShow()
        Called when the FileEditor is about to be shown. Calls Ode.getInstance().setCurrentFileEditor(this). The subclass should do anything else necessary to get its UI set up after calling super.onShow().

      • onHide

        public void onHide()
        Called when the FileEditor is about to be hidden. Calls Ode.getInstance().setCurrentFileEditor(null). The subclass should do anything else necessary to get its UI cleaned up after calling super.onHide().

      • onClose

        public void onClose()
        Called when the FileEditor is about to be closed. Subclasses can override this to remove themselves as listeners.

      • startRepl

        public void startRepl(boolean alreadyRunning,
             boolean forEmulator,
             boolean forUsb)
        Called to trigger the Repl (Wireless) to start. This version does nothing but the YaBlocksEditor overrides this version with one that start the Repl going.

      • getRawFileContent

        public abstract String getRawFileContent()
        Gets the raw content of the file associated with the editor. This method is used when the EditorManager saves modified files.

        public abstract void onSave()
        Invoked after a save operation completes successfully.
